  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "# Rationale\r\n\r\n`--prune.*.before` would keep all receipts, history, etc, from a given block on, but not before it.\r\n\r\nThis is useful for integrating with Ethereum PoS consensus clients, which need eth_getLogs about deposits since genesis, block \"11052984\" on the PoW chain.\r\n\r\n`--prune.*.before` and `--prune.*.older` would be mutually exclusive. While `older` keeps the last N; `before` would keep everything since N, including N: The threshold would not move with the tip of the chain. This is useful for any dApp or contract that cares about \"transactions since deployment\".",
