    "body": "Based on the situation described in #2506, it would be awesome to (also) have an option like `--prune-so-that-eth2-works`, which may become increasingly important in the (near) future. Basically it would tell `erigon` to keep the minimum amount of data that makes deposit queries (and everything related to staking configuration / launchpad steps) work just fine. (Completeness or usefulness of data irrelevant for Eth2 would not be much of a concern; the less data the better.)",
